    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-03-25T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-03-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="68"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d68">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 832.73/143</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Vice Consul in Charge at Rio de Janeiro</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Momsen</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 1249</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rio de Janeiro</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-03-25">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 25, 1918</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to despatch No. 1068 of December 17,
                        1917,<note n="1" xml:id="d68fn1">Not printed.</note> from this Consulate
                    General, I have the honor to report that there was <pb facs="0177" n="65"
                        xml:id="pg_65"/> published in the <hi rend="italic">Diario Official</hi>
                    (Official Gazette) of March 14, 1918, an order of the Minister of Transportation
                    and Public Works— <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p rend="flushleft">granting to Mr. Nelson O’Shaughnessy, representative of
                            the Western Union Telegraph Co., for the company or for any other
                            company which may be organized, permission, without monopoly or special
                            privilege of any kind, to lay and operate two submarine cables from the
                            city of Nictheroy (which is the capital of the State of Rio de Janeiro,
                            and situated directly across the bay from this city): one with landing
                            places on the island of Itaparica, the city of Aracajú, the island of
                            Fernando de Noronha, the cities of Parahyba, Natal and Belem, and from
                            there to the Greater Antilles; and another from Nictheroy to the city of
                            Paranagua, to be connected with Maldonado in the Republic of Uruguay,
                            with permission to be prolonged to the Republic Argentina.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">R. P. Momsen</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
